  <bodyText><![CDATA[<div class="g12"><img src="/media/13054464/amalfi-explorer-tour.jpg" alt="Amalfi Coast Splendours" rel="879,452" /></div>
<div> </div>
<!--start left column-->
<div class="g8">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p style="text-align: center; font-size: 20px; font-weight: bold;">For more information or to book this Explorer Holiday please call 01483 345 805</p>
<p>This Explorer Holiday gives you the opportunity to stay on perhaps <em>the</em> most beautiful coastline in the world with included days out to see the local sites. Join your friendly Representative to visit Pompeii, Vesuvius and Paestum as well as to travel into the hills to taste some of the fabulous local wine. Your hotel is located in the charming resort of Maiori and there’s plenty of free time to relax and soak up the atmosphere of this wonderful region.</p>
<p> </p>
<h2>HIGHLIGHTS</h2>
<ul>
<li>7 nights in the 4 star <a href="https://www.inghamsitaly.co.uk/destinations/neapolitan-riviera/amalfi-coast/hotel-reginna-palace/"><strong>Hotel Reginna Palace</strong></a> in Maiori on half board</li>
<li>Free days to relax on the beach or beside the pool</li>
<li>Full day to visit the fascinating Roman site of <a href="https://www.inghamsitaly.co.uk/destinations/neapolitan-riviera/pompei-mount-vesuvius-and-herculaneum/">Pompeii</a> and Mount Vesuvius.</li>
<li>Visit the hilltop village of Ravello with its famous views of the coast</li>
<li>Wine tasting included</li>
<li>Visit Paestum famous for its Greek temples</li>
<li>See mozzarella made</li>
<li>Boat trip to Capri (optional)</li>
<li>Amalfi town and Positano can easily be reached by public transport</li>
</ul>
<p> </p>
<h2>ITINERARY</h2>
<p><strong>Day 1 | </strong>Fly to Naples and transfer to your hotel in Maiori. In the evening meet your fellow travellers and your Inghams Representative.</p>
<p><strong>Day 2 | </strong>This morning we visit the nearby village of Ravello<strong>,</strong> famous for its wonderful views of the Amalfi Coast. We then continue into the Lattari Mountains to Tramonti for a light lunch and to taste some of the lovely local wine.</p>
<p><strong>Day 3 | </strong>Today you have a free day to explore Maiori, a small town founded by the Etruscans, and also to enjoy the hotel’s pool and private beach (local charge).</p>
<p><strong>Day 4 | </strong>A full day’s excursion to visit the Roman archaeological site of Pompeii with a local guide. This is followed by a visit to Mount Vesuvius, a fascinating volcano that erupted in AD79 destroying Pompeii.</p>
<p><strong>Day 5 | </strong>Today you may wish to join your Representative for an optional boat trip to the island of Capri.</p>
<p><strong>Day 6 | </strong>Today travel south to visit the Greek temples of Paestum which are considered to be the best in Italy. This area, called the Cilento, is well known for the production of mozzarella cheese and we visit a local dairy farm to see how it's made.</p>
<p><strong>Day 7 | </strong>Today is another day at leisure and you could take the chance to visit nearby Amalfi or take a boat to beautiful Positano with its colourful houses clinging to the cliffs.</p>
<p><strong>Day 8 | </strong>Transfer to Naples airport for your return flight or maybe extend your stay and create your own multi-centre holiday, perhaps with a few days in Sorrento or Rome.</p>
</div>
</div>
